1) Download VMware Workstation from download website : 
https://www.vmware.com/products/workstation-pro/workstation-pro-evaluation.html



2) Download Ubuntu from ubuntu direct site : 
https://ubuntu.com/download/desktop/thank-you?version=20.04.3&architecture=amd64



Enter the BIOS interface: 
Press the shortcut Delete/ F12 continuously while booting the computer. 
Click <Advanced>-> <Processor> (CPU)-> 
Virtual or Virtualization, 
for some computers, 
VT are included in Configuration or Security. 
Set the VT option to Enabled.
Press Save (usually F10) to save and exit (Save & Exit)
